item.title: CVE-2019-6555|2024-08-04T20:23:21.951Z -- ics-cert -- cscape
item.description: Cscape, 9.80 SP4 and prior. An improper input validation vulnerability may be exploited by processing specially crafted POC files. This may allow an attacker to read confidential information and remotely execute arbitrary code.
